        <h2 style="color: white;" ><u>Problem</u></h2>
           <p style="color: white; font-size: 17px; text-align: justify">
        This Competition consists of two stages:
        <h3 style="color: white;"> <u>STAGE 1 : THE CONSTRUCTION STAGE</u>:- </h3>
        <p style="color: white; font-size: 17px; text-align: justify">
        In this stage each team will be provided a problem statement according to which they have to construct a structure with the desired specifications. Marks are assigned to the strength, architecture, the use of material and aesthetics.
        <h3 style="color: white;"> <u>STAGE 2 : THE JUDGING STAGE</u>:- </h3>
      <p style="color: white; font-size: 17px; text-align: justify">   Judging would include
        <ul style="color: white;" class="style6">
 
                <li> Creative score. </li>
                <li> Load Test Score. </li></ul>
         <h3 style="color: white;font-size:15px"> <u>Creative Score</u> </h3>
         <p style="color: white;font-size:15px"> Creative score includes:
         <ul style="color: white;font-size:15px"> 
				<li> Stability of structure.   </li>
                <li> Innovations.    </li>
                <li> Design of structure as per problem statement (strictly). </li></ul>
                <p style="color: white;font-size:15px">The creative score would be given by judges and it will be subjective. The decision of judges will be final.
            </ul>
           <h3 style="color: white;font-size:15px">  <u>Load Test Score</u> </h3>
<p style="color: white;font-size:15px">A load test will be conducted and teams will be awarded score on the basis of the load it can safely bear.

<h3 style="color: white;"> <u>FAILURE CRITERIA</u>:- </h3>
<p style="color: white; font-size: 17px">A structure fails if: 
<ul style="color: white;" class="style6">

<li> The structure fails to satisfy any of the constraints given for the structure. </li> 
<li> The structure breaks (or any Popsicle stick) or is not in a condition to carry the load over it. </li>
 </ul>
 
